In [28]:
def discard_users(users, sessions, payments, levels, id_list):
    users = users[~users['user_id'].isin(id_list)]
    sessions = sessions[~sessions['user_id'].isin(id_list)]
    payments = payments[~payments['user_id'].isin(id_list)]
    levels = levels[~levels['user_id'].isin(id_list)]
    
    return(users, sessions, payments, levels)

def count_losses(users, sessions, payments, levels, 
                 users_init, sessions_init, payments_init, levels_init):
    print('users\n')
    print(f' : {users_init.shape[0] - users.shape[0]} ({((users_init.shape[0] - users.shape[0]) / users_init.shape[0]):.1%})')
    print('-' * 50)
    
    print('sessions\n')
    print(f' : {sessions_init.shape[0] - sessions.shape[0]} ({((sessions_init.shape[0] - sessions.shape[0]) / sessions_init.shape[0]):.1%})')
    print(f' : {sessions_init.user_id.nunique() - sessions.user_id.nunique()} ({((sessions_init.user_id.nunique() - sessions.user_id.nunique()) / sessions_init.user_id.nunique()):.1%})')
    print('-' * 50)
    
    print('payments\n')
    print(f' : {payments_init.shape[0] - payments.shape[0]} ({((payments_init.shape[0] - payments.shape[0]) / payments_init.shape[0]):.1%})')
    print(f' : {payments_init.user_id.nunique() - payments.user_id.nunique()} ({((payments_init.user_id.nunique() - payments.user_id.nunique()) / payments_init.user_id.nunique()):.1%})')
    print('-' * 50)
    
    print('levels\n')
    print(f' : {levels_init.shape[0] - levels.shape[0]} ({((levels_init.shape[0] - levels.shape[0]) / levels_init.shape[0]):.1%})')
    print(f' : {levels_init.user_id.nunique() - levels.user_id.nunique()} ({((levels_init.user_id.nunique() - levels.user_id.nunique()) / levels_init.user_id.nunique()):.1%})')
    print('-' * 50)
    
    print('total\n')
    print(f' : {users_init.shape[0] + sessions_init.shape[0] + payments_init.shape[0] + levels_init.shape[0] - users.shape[0] - sessions.shape[0] - payments.shape[0] - levels.shape[0]} ({((users_init.shape[0] + sessions_init.shape[0] + payments_init.shape[0] + levels_init.shape[0] - users.shape[0] - sessions.shape[0] - payments.shape[0] - levels.shape[0]) / (users_init.shape[0] + sessions_init.shape[0] + payments_init.shape[0] + levels_init.shape[0])):.1%})')

def lifetime_calculation(df, column):
    df = df.merge(users[['user_id', 'reg_time']], on='user_id', how='left')
    df['lifetime'] = (df[column] - df.reg_time).dt.days
    return(df)
